                                    <amp-img noloading height=400 width=400 layout=responsive src="/images/QL-Box_User_IN-6014HD.png"></amp-img>
                                  </a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="action">
                                  <h4>Schützen Sie Ihre Privatsphäre</h4>
                                  <p class="justify">Stellen Sie bitte sicher, dass Sie das Standard-Login Ihrer Kamera vor der Durchleitung Ihrer Kamera zum Internet ändern. Ändern Sie das Kennwort aller 3 Logins - Administrator, User und Visitor - damit sich niemand mit Ihrer Kamera verbinden kann, der nicht Ihre Erlaubnis hat. Sie können immer den Hardware Reset Ihrer Kamera nutzen, sollten Sie Ihr vergessen haben.<br><br></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <!-- /card-container -->

                            <div class="card-container">
                                <div class="onecard">
                                    <div class="image">
                                      <a href="/Internet_Access/Port_Forwarding">
                                        <amp-img role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/Portforwarding_Box.png" width="900" height="650" layout="responsive"></amp-img>
                                      </a>
                                      <div class="action">
                                          <p>In general we have to differentiate between two types of connections. One connection is the internal access which with we access the WebUI of the camera. This means that the computer as well as the camera are running in the same network and are most likely connected to the same router. You can then connect to the camera using the private IP address of the camera. The other connection is the external access to open the WebUI of the camera from outside your network. With this connection you can allow the access from anywhere in the world to your camera. No matter if you are sitting in the train using a smartphone or if you are on holidays using a laptop to access.</p>
                                      </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
